ly%20Mail%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20started%20in%20September%202021%2C%20when%20Jovanovic%2C%20an%20LA%20dentist%2C%20approved%20a%20long-term%20stay%20for%20Elizabeth%20Hirschhorn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHirschhorn%20rented%20the%20guesthouse%20for%20six%20months%20at%20%24105%20per%20night%2C%20spending%20%2420%2C793%20in%20total%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20months%20in%2C%20however%2C%20Jovanic%20offered%20to%20put%20Hirschhorn%20up%20in%20a%20hotel%20while%20a%20contractor%20made%20some%20repairs.%20Hirschhorn%20declined%2C%20and%20she%20also%20declined%20an%20offer%20to%20stay%20at%20his%20home%2C%20per%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20tense%20exchange%20ensued%20until%20Hirschhorn's%20originally%20scheduled%20Airbnb%20stay%20ended%20on%20March%2019%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20the%20pair%20agreed%20to%20extend%20her%20stay%20until%20April%2012%2C%202022%2C%20while%20she%20looked%20for%20another%20property%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExtending%20the%20lease%20beyond%20March%2019%20meant%20that%20Airbnb%20would%20not%20be%20involved.%20Airbnb%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2012%2C%20Hirschhorn%20stopped%20paying%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Times%2C%20around%20this%20time%20Hirschhorn%20contacted%20the%20Department%20of%20Building%20and%20Safety%2C%20which%20identified%20two%20code%20violations%3A%20lack%20of%20approval%20for%20occupancy%20and%20an%20unpermitted%20shower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20submitted%20a%20complaint%20to%20a%20city%20official%2C%20alleging%20illegal%20eviction%2C%20harassment%2C%20and%20nonpayment%20of%20relocation%20fees%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20agreed%20that%20because%20the%20unit%20violated%20city%20codes%2C%20Jovanovic%20had%20to%20withdraw%20his%20eviction%20notices%20until%20he%20could%20prove%20that%20the%20unit%20was%20in%20compliance%2C%20per%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Hirschhorn%20won't%20allow%20him%20inside%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Hirschhorn%20having%20been%20in%20the%20property%20for%20more%20than%20six%20months%2C%20she%20also%20qualifies%20for%20LA's%20new%20Just%20Cause%20Ordinance%2C%20which%20requires%20a%20landlord%20to%20give%20a%20legal%20reason%20for%20eviction%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20none%20exists%2C%20the%20landlord%20must%20pay%20for%20relocation%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20city%20official%20concluded%20that%20the%20property%20was%20subject%20to%20LA's%20Rent%20Stabilization%20Ordinance%2C%20affording%20Hirschhorn%20more%20substantial%20tenant%20protections%2C%20per%20the%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJovanovic%20and%20his%20lawyer%2C%20Sebastian%20Rucci%2C%20have%20attempted%20to%20sue%20Hirschhorn%20on%20two%20fronts%3A%20a%20damages%20complaint%20to%20recover%20unpaid%20rent%2C%20and%20an%20unlawful%20detainer%20complaint%20to%20evict%20her%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHirschhorn's%20legal%20team%20successfully%20had%20the%20latter%20dismissed%20by%20a%20judge%2C%20though%20Jovanovic's%20legal%20team%20is%20appealing%20the%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe's%20the%20tenant%20from%20hell%2C%26quot%3B%20Rucci%20told%20the%20Times.%20%26quot%3BIf%20she's%20right%2C%20the%20theory%20is%20that%20if%20a%20landlord%20has%20something%20that%20isn't%20permitted%2C%20then%20you%20can%20stay%20in%20it%20rent-free%20forever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHirschhorn's%20attorney%2C%20Colin%20Walshok%2C%20told%20the%20newspaper%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20landlord%20broke%20the%20law%20and%20tried%20to%20make%20money%20by%20renting%20out%20an%20illegal%20bootleg%20unit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20he%20was%20caught%2C%20instead%20of%20doing%20the%20right%20thing%2C%20he%20has%20resorted%20to%20bullying%2C%20harassment%2C%20and%20the%20filing%20of%20frivolo