le%20CEO%20Tim%20Cook%20just%20sold%20%2488%20million%20of%20his%20stock%2C%20earning%20about%20%2441.5%20million%20after%20taxes.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20iPhone%20maker's%20boss%20cashed%20in%2013%25%20of%20his%20stake%2C%20but%20still%20owns%20shares%20worth%20%24570%20million.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3ECook%20was%20awarded%20the%20shares%20for%20delivering%20a%20total%20shareholder%20return%20of%C2%A0%2054.1%25%20over%20three%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Faapl-stock%5C%22%3EApple%3C%2Fa%3E%20CEO%20Tim%20Cook%20has%20cashed%20in%2013%25%20of%20his%20stake%20in%20the%20iPhone%20maker%20for%20about%20%2441.5%20million%20after%20taxes%2C%20marking%20his%20biggest%20share%20sale%20in%20over%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20technology%20titan's%20boss%20has%20sold%20511%2C000%20shares%20of%20Apple%20this%20month%2C%20at%20prices%20between%20%24170%20and%20%24174%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F320193%2F000032019323000089%2FxslF345X05%2Fwk-form4_1696381457.xml%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregulatory%20filing%3C%2Fa%3E%20revealed%20on%20Wednesday.%20The%20disposals%20generated%20around%20%2488%20million%20of%20gross%20proceeds%2C%20but%20roughly%20%2444%20million%20was%20withheld%20by%20Apple%20to%20cover%20the%20taxes%20incurred.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20was%20awarded%20restricted%20stock%20units%20(RSUs)%20in%20September%202020%20that%20would%20only%20convert%20into%20common%20stock%20if%20he%20met%20certain%20performance%20goals.%20His%20target%20was%20to%20achieve%20a%20total%20shareholder%20return%20(TSR)%20%E2%80%94%20Apple's%20stock-price%20performance%20with%20dividends%20reinvested%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%2055th%20percentile%20of%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20companies%20over%20a%20three-year%20period%2C%20in%20which%20case%20he%20would%20receive%20334%2C000%20RSUs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20Apple