e%20said.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20all%20paths%20that%20could%20eventually%20lead%20participants%20out%20of%20poverty%20and%20allow%20them%20to%20be%20less%20dependent%20on%20social%20support%20programs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDonovan%20founded%20the%20Denver%20Basic%20Income%20Project%20in%202021.%20An%20entrepreneur%2C%20he%20made%20his%20money%20off%20Wooden%20Ships%2C%20a%20clothing%20company%20that%20specializes%20in%20sweaters%20for%20women%2C%20and%20an%20investment%20in%20Tesla%20that%20skyrocketed%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20He%20used%20some%20of%20that%20cash%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.9news.com%2Farticle%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Fnext%2Fnext-with-kyle-clark%2Fdenver-basic-income-launch-2-million-from-city%2F73-7ecf04aa-c51a-444b-88ea-48b91b136568%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%242%20million%20contribution%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20city%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0to%20actually%20begin%20distributing%20money%20to%20others%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommentary%20on%20homelessness%20often%20focuses%20on%20mental%20health%20and%20addiction%2C%20perceived%20as%20the%20chief%20drivers%20of%20a%20spike%20in%20people%20sleeping%20on%20the%20streets%20in%20cities%20from%20Sacramento%20to%20Jacksonville.%20But%20as%20the%20Pew%20Charitable%20Trust%20noted%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewtrusts.org%2Fen%2Fresearch-and-analysis%2Farticles%2F2023%2F08%2F22%2Fhow-housing-costs-drive-levels-of-homelessness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20research%20has%20%26quot%3Bconsistently%20found%20that%20homelessness%20in%20an%20area%20is%20driven%20by%20housing%20costs%26quot%3B%20(i.e.%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-poverty-in-philadelphia-says-about-homelessness-in-los-angeles-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20rent%2C%20not%20the%20weather%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20months%20in%2C%20most%20who%20received%20money%20from%20the%20project%20were%20better%20off%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0significantly%20so%2C%20according%20to%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Denver's%20Center%20for%20Housing%20and%20Homelessness%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Denver's%20universal%20basic%20income%20plan%20worked%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20October%2C%20more%20than%20800%20people%20were%20enrolled%20in%20the%20basic%20income%20plan%2C%20but%20they%20did%20not%20all%20receive%20the%20same%20stipend.%20There%20are%20three%20groups%3A%20One%20receives%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20a%20year%3B%20another%20receives%20%246%2C500%20up%20front%20and%20then%20%24500%20a%20month%20from%20there%3B%20and%20another%20gets%20just%20%2450%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20cautioning%20that%20this%20is%20only%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1gqtOfZG2sSanWgUdzn-lx-pwSXZKabj-%2Fview%3Fpli%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterim%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20what%20is%20a%20yearlong%20study%2C%20the%20researchers%20nonetheless%20found%20stark%20and%20encouraging%20changes%20in%20participants'%20material%20conditions.%20Those%20that%20received%20%24500%20or%20more%20per%20month%20saw%20the%20biggest%20gains.%20At%20the%20start%2C%20fewer%20than%2010%25%20were%20living%20in%20their%20own%20home%20or%20apartment%2C%20while%20at%20the%20six-month%20point%2C%20more%20than%20a%20third%20lived%20in%20their%20own%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20guaranteed%20income%20also%20dramatically%20reduced%20visible%20homelessness.%20When%20the%20initiative%20began%2C%20some%206%25%20of%20the%20people%20in%20the%20%241%2C000%2Fmonth%20group%20were%20sleeping%20outside%3B%20the%20number%20fell%20to%20zero%20six%20months%20later.%20The%20group%20that%20received%20a%20large%20lump%20sum%20similarly%20reported%20a%20decline%20from%2010%25%20sleeping%20outdoors%20to%203%25.%20Even%20those%20who%20received%20just%20%2450%20moved%20indoors%2C%20to%20a%20degree%2C%20the%20rat