20Donbas%20region%2C%20on%20March%209%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651e25a9617692f0d03fa018%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20serviceman%20walks%20on%20a%20muddy%20road%20near%20Bakhmut%20in%20the%20Donbas%20region%2C%20on%20March%209%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EARIS%20MESSINIS%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20fighting%20stops%2C%20he%20noted.%20The%20tempo%20may%20be%20slower%20or%20there%20may%20be%20increased%20difficulty%20in%20conducting%20mechanized%20warfare%20with%20tanks%20and%20artillery%2C%20but%20Ukraine%20has%20indicated%20their%20intent%20to%20continue%20fighting%20through%20whatever%20comes%20so%20its%20forces%20do%20not%20lose%20any%20of%20the%20momentum%20they%20have%20been%20building%20over%20the%20past%20few%20months.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKyiv's%20troops%20could%20opt%20to%20use%20the%20same%20tactics%20they've%20been%20using%20to%20push%20against%20Russian%20defenses%20in%20the%20south%20over%20the%20past%20few%20weeks%2C%20tactics%20involving%20infantry%20advancing%20on%20foot%20with%20less%20reliance%20on%20tanks%20and%20fighting%20vehicles%2C%20but%20that%C2%A0is%20difficult%20to%20predict%20on%20an%20ever-changing%20battlefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20too%20early%20to%20tell%20how%20wet%20the%20mud%20season%20will%20be%20%E2%80%94%20it'll%20depend%20on%20precipitation%20levels%2C%20and%20like%20any%20other%20larger%20country%2C%20Ukraine's%20different%20regions%20have%20varied%20climate%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESouthern%20Ukraine%2C%20specifically%20areas%20around%20the%20Zaporizhzhia%20region%2C%20is%20one%20of%20the%20driest%20parts%20of%20the%20nation%2C%20according%20to%20historical%20meteorological%20data%2C%20with%20the%20oblast%20receiving%20little%20rainfall%20in%20comparison%20to%20areas%20in%20western%20Ukraine%20like%20Kyiv%20or%20regions%20to%20the%20northeast%20such%20as%20Kharkiv.%C2%A0So%20the%20Abrams%20may%20not%20even%20encounter%20thick%20mud%2C%20but%20it's%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22American%20military%20stand%20in%20front%20of%20a%20Abrams%20tank%20before%20a%20live%20fire%20demonstration%20part%20of%20the%20Bear%2022%20military%20exercises%20at%20the%20Nowa%20Deba%20training%20ground%20on%20September%2021%2C%202022%2C%20in%20Nowa%20Deba%2C%20Poland.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651d83362ce014759e7491b0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmerican%20military%20stand%20in%20front%20of%20a%20Abrams%20tank%20before%20a%20live%20fire%20demonstration%20part%20of%20the%20Bear%2022%20military%20exercises%20at%20the%20Nowa%20Deba%20training%20ground%20on%20September%2021%2C%202022%2C%20in%20Nowa%20Deba%2C%20Poland.%3Cp%3EOmar%20Marques%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20A1%20weighing%20in%20at%2060%20tons%2C%20it%20is%20among%20the%20heaviest%20tanks%20in%20the%20Ukrainian%20arsenal%20and%20significantly%20heavier%20than%20Ukraine's%20Soviet%20armor.%20The%20T-72%2C%20for%20example%2C%20weighs%20in%20around%2045%20tons.%20And%20the%20T-64%20that%20Ukraine%20reported%20got%20stuck%20last%20spring%20weighs%20less%20than%2040%20tons.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20because%20it%20is%20heavy%20doesn't%20mean%20it's%20more%20at%20risk%20of%20being%20swallowed%20up%20by%20mud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20irony%20is%20that%20tanks%20are%20not%20particularly%20susceptible%20to%20mud%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Cancian%2C%20a%20senior%20advisor%20with%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20and%20a%20retired%20Marine%20Corps%20colonel%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20designed%20to%20operate%20cross-country%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20with%20wide%20tracks%20spreading%20the%20tank's%20weight%20across%20a%20wider%20area.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20Abrams'%20ground%20pressure%2C%20or%20how%20much%20force%20its%20weight%20is%20exerting%20over%20a%20given%20area%2C%20is%20quite%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222592%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Abrams%20tank%20from%201st%20battalion%2C%208th%20Cavalry%20Regiment%2C%20drives%20into%20the%20woods%20during%20Combined%20Resolve%20XIII%20(CBRXIII)%20at%20the%20Joint%20Multinational%20Readiness%20Center%20Hohenfels%2C%20Germany%2C%20on%20Feb.%2002%2C%202002.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651e2241617692f0d03f9e94%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221728%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Abrams%20tank%20from%201st%20battalion%2C%208th%20Cavalry%20Regiment%2C%20drives%20into%20the%20woods%20during%20Combined%20Resolve%20XIII%20(CBRXIII)%20at%20the%20Joint%20Multinational%20Readiness%20Center%20Hohenfels%2C%20Germany%2C%20on%20Feb.%2002%2C%202002.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20still%20a%20risk%20of%20it%20getting%20caught%20in%20mud%2C%20especially%20off%20road.%20But%20the%20Abrams%20features%20capabilities%20to%20keep%20it%20from%20getting%20stuck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20does%20the%20tank%20have%20a%20powerful%20gas-turbine%20engine%2C%20but%20the%20tracks%20and%20suspension%20systems%20were%20designed%20to%20allow%20the%20tank%20to%20move%20and%20fight%20across%20varied%20terrain%2C%20giving%20it%20maneuverability%20and%20agility%C2%A0despite%20its%20heavy%20weight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.dtic.mil%2Fsti%2Fpdfs%2FADA039673.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1974%20military%20evaluation%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20XM1%20program%2C%20which%20eventually%20gave%20birth%20to%20the%20M1%20Abrams%2C%20looked%20into%20the%20potential%20role%20of%20a%20new%20American%20tank%20on%20the%20battlefield%20and%20noted%20that%20%26quot%3Bmilitary%20planners%20both%20western%20and%20Soviet%20still%20consider%20the%20tank%20the%20key%20weapon%20in%20ground%20combat.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20the%20US%20had%20to%20prioritize%20fielding%20a%20tank%20%26quot%3Bcapable%20of%20dominating%20and%20defeating%20the%20enormous%20threat%20inherent%20in%20the%20armor%20of%20our%20potential%20adversaries.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20built%20in%20the%20late%201970s%2C%20the%20Abrams%20was%20designed%20to%20give%20US%20forces%20the%20edge%20over%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20in%20land%20warfare.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20made%20for%20central%20European%20plains%20against%20Soviets%2C%26quot%3B%20Greenway%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20its%20single%20focus%20design%20parameter.%20It'll%20obviously%20work%20in%20other%20environments%2C%20and%20it%20has%2C%20but%20it%20was%20made%20to%20do%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225041%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20Abrams%20tank%20races%20across%20the%20Adazi%20military%20training%20area%2C%20Latvia%20on%20March%2023%2C%202021%2C%20to%20take%20an%20objective%20during%20exercise%20Crystal%20Arrow.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651e24a52ce014759e7552c9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223148%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Abrams%20tank%20races%20across%20the%20Adazi%20military%20training%20area%2C%20Latvia%20on%20March%2023%2C%202021%2C%20to%20take%20an%20objective%20during%20exercise%20Crystal%20Arrow.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20again%2C%20another%20key%20advantage%20of%20the%20Abrams%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20muddy%20terrain%2C%20is%20its%20powerful%20gas-turbine%20engine%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20compared%20to%20a%20jet%20engine.%20It%20guzzles%20much%20more%20fuel%20than%20a%20diesel%20engine%2C%20especially%20while%20idle%2C%20but%20it%20can%20get%20the%20M1A1%20up%20to%20about%2045%20miles%20an%20hour.%2