20decade%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Center%20for%20Education%20Statistics.%20With%20majors%20like%20Chaos%2C%20Human%20Computer%20Interaction%2C%20and%20Architecture%20and%20Food%20Theory%2C%20students%20aren't%20just%20crafting%20these%20degrees%20for%20fun.%20Where%20customized%20majors%20used%20to%20be%20about%20specialization%2C%20today%2C%20for%20many%20young%20people%2C%20forging%20a%20unique%20educational%20route%20is%20about%20adapting%20to%20a%20constantly%20transforming%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-employers-quiet-quitting-contractors-part-time-gig-2023-6%5C%22%3Efull-time%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20replaced%20by%20contract%20gigs%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-hustle-generation-jobs-work-side-hustle-freelance-2023-5%5C%22%3Eside%20hustles%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20become%20increasingly%20necessary%20to%20get%20ahead%20financially.%20Meanwhile%2C%20as%20artificial%20intelligence%20threatens%20to%20upend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-radically-reshape-job-market-global-economy-employee-labor-innovation-2023-8%5C%22%3Eroughly%20300%20million%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20employers%20are%20placing%20a%20premium%20on%20individuality%20and%20flexibility.%20Increasingly%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20pivot%20is%20a%20must-have%20for%20workers%20to%20survive.%20And%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20students%20believe%20the%20best%20way%20to%20show%20self-motivation%20and%20creativity%20is%20a%20personally%20crafted%20college%20degree.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFlexibility%20is%20the%20new%20major%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20junior%20year%20at%20the%20Rochester%20Institution%20of%20Technology%2C%20Oluwaseyi%20Onifade%20was%20struggling%20to%20find%20a%20degree%20that%20perfectly%20fit%20his%20interest%20in%20healthcare%20and%20biotechnology.%20After%20speaking%20with%20his%20dean%2C%20Onifade%20learned%20about%20RIT's%20School%20of%20Individualized%20Study%2C%20which%20allowed%20him%20to%20combine%20courses%20in%20business%20administration%20and%20public%20health%20to%20create%20his%20own%20field%20of%20study%20%E2%80%94%20all%20while%20encouraging%20him%20to%20take%20classes%20outside%20these%20fields%20that%20might%20be%20relevant%20to%20his%20career%20interests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnifade%2C%20who%20plans%20to%20graduate%20with%20a%20custom-made%20degree%20in%20global%20health%20management%20and%20healthcare%20administration%20at%20the%20end%20of%20this%20school%20year%2C%20said%20he%20liked%20the%20flexible%20nature%20of%20the%20program%20and%20felt%20that%20pursuing%20his%20own%20major%20nurtured%20skills%20directly%20applicable%20to%20his%20interests.%20He%20also%20said%20the%20program%20can%20be%20a%20double-edged%20sword.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20come%20to%20a%20school%20like%20this%20if%20you%20don't%20know%20what%20you%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20Onifade%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20my%20own%20boss%2C%20but%20sometimes%20a%20boss%20can't%20get%20everything%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EOne%20of%20the%20craziest%20parts%20of%20the%20system%20is%20that%20we%20expect%2017-year-olds%20to%20know%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3ERIT's%20customized%20program%20has%20seen%20an%20explosion%20in%20students%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%20%E2%80%94%20enrollment%20in%20the%20program%20grew%2045%25%20from%202019%20to%202021.%20James%20Hall%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20school%20explained%20there%20are%20three%20main%20types%20of%20students%20entering%20RIT's%20SOIS%20program%3A%20students%20who%20want%20to%20explore%20less%20traditionally%20congruent%20academic%20interests%2C%20students%20pursuing%20a%20hyper-specific%20area%20of%20study%2C%20and%20students%20that%20are%20just%20looking%20to%20pool%20their%20credits%20in%20order%20to%20graduate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20get%20to%20pick%20and%20choose%20courses%20from%20across%20departments%20to%20curate%20their%20major%2C%20but%20they're%20also%20required%20to%20take%20a%20handful%20of%20standardized%20courses%20that%20offer%20a%20foundation%20for%20their%20learning%20%E2%80%94%20classes%20%26quot%3Bthat%20can%20adapt%20to%20evolving%20career%20fields%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20school%20site%20advertises.%20One%20course%2C%20Individuals%20and%20Society%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20aims%20to%20%26quot%3Btake%20a%20student's%20interests%20into%20the%20workforce%26quot%3B%20by%20teaching%20them%20how%20to%20%26quot%3Breflect%20and%20market%20themselves%2C%26quot%3B%20Makini%20Beck%2C%20the%20professor%20who%20teaches%20the%20course%2C%20said.%20Another%20course%2C%20Ethics%20in%20Leadership%2C%20helps%20students%20examine%20current%20societal%20dilemmas%20faced%20by%20business%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20these%20courses%2C%20SOIS%20helps%20students%20prepare%20for%20a%20long%20career%20of%20networking%2C%20learning%2C%20and%20adapting.%20%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20craziest%20parts%20of%20the%20system%20is%20that%20we%20expect%2017-year-olds%20to%20know%20what%20they%20want%20to%20do%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20Hall%20told%20me.%20By%20equipping%20students%20with%20the%20skills%20they%20need%20to%20adapt%20to%20an%20evolving%20economy%2C%20the%20logic%20goes%2C%20they%20will%20be%20better%20prepared%20for%20their%20career.%20%26quot%3BContinuous%20learning%20is%20the%20reality%20we%20all%20live%20with%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Hall%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnifade%20echoed%20that%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20program%20is%20not%20just%20about%20being%20in%20college%2C%20it's%20about%20what%20happens%20after.%26quot%3B%20Even%20as%20a%20student%2C%20he's%20felt%20that%20impact%20already%2C%20saying%20the%20courses%20he%20took%20that%20taught%20collaboration%20skills%20gave%20him%20a%20leg%20up%20in%20his%20various%20work%20experiences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAn%20eye%20on%20the%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20build-your-own%20majors%20is%20a%20logical%20response%20to%20a%20job%20market%20that%20prioritizes%20self-invention%20%E2%80%94%20and%20self-reinvention.%20According%20to%20the%20World%20Economic%20Forum's%202023%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Freports%2Fthe-future-of-jobs-report-2023%3Fgclid%3DEAIaIQobChMI5ouah9CSgQMV0zrUAR0fsQOrEAAYASAAEgLGHPD_BwE%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFuture%20of%20Jobs%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20employers%20said%20they%20anticipated%2023%25%20of%20jobs%20to%20be%20disrupted%20in%20the%20next%20five%20years.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20employers%20rated%20self-efficacy%20skills%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20resilience%2C%20flexibility%2C%20and%20agility%20%E2%80%94%20among%20the%20top-three%20most%20important%20skills%20for%20workers.%20Ben%20Papernick%2C%20a%20recruiter%20with%20over%2015%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20tech%20and%20marketing%2C%20said%20he%20looks%20for%20candidates%20who%20demonstrate%20a%20balance%20between%20subject%20expertise%20and%20resilience.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20look%20for%20people%20that%20are%20ambitious%2C%20who%20have%20drive.%20Do%20they%20have%20the%20hard%20skills%20that%20we're%20looking%20for%3F%20But%20more%20importantly%2C%20do%20you%20have%20the%20soft%20skills%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Papernick%20said%20students%20who%20created%20their%20own%20majors%20were%20off%20to%20an%20impressive%20start.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20take%20the%20time%2C%20do%20the%20research%2C%20put%20a%20master%20plan%20together%20and%20complete%20them%20with%20merit%20%E2%80%94%20hats%20off%20to%20you.%20It%20shows%20versatility%20and%20eagerness%20to%20learn.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20flexibility%20is%20key%20to%20stay%20on%20top%20of%20a%20churning%20job%20market%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-not-going-to-college-tuition-costs-higher-education-2023-9%5C%22%3Ecolleges%3C%2Fa%3E%20haven't%20been%20able%20to%20move%20fast%20enough%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20emerging%20trends.%20The%20number%20of%20students%20working%20in%20an%20industry%20closely%20related%20to%20their%20major%20four%20years%20after%20graduation%20dropped%208%20percentage%20points%20between%201997%20and%202012%2C%20the%20National%20Center%20for%20Education%20Statistics%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnces.ed.gov%2Fpubs2018%2F2018163.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Considering%20that%20it%20can%20take%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feab.com%2Finsights%2Fblogs%2Foperations%2Fto-grow-academic-programs-profitably-ask-these-questions-first%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esix%20years%20and%20%242.2%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20college%20to%20develop%20a%20single%20degree%20program%2C%20it%20makes%20sense%20that%20schools%20are%20trying%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20evolving%20workforce%20demands%20by%20teaching%20students%20flexibility%20instead%20of%20pivoting%20entire%20degree%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EIf%20you%20take%20the%20time%2C%20do%20the%20research%2C%20put%20a%20master%20plan%20together%20and%20complete%20them%20with%20merit%20%E2%80%94%20hats%20off%20to%20you.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20RIT%20renamed%20its%20individualized%20major%20the%20New%20Economy%20major%20and%20highlighted%20the%20need%20for%20students%20to%20%26quot%3Badapt%20to%20evolving%20career%20fields.%26quot%3B%20The%20same%20year%2C%20Genesee%20Community%20College%20in%20Western%20New%20York%20announced%20a%20new%20Individualized%20Studies%20Degree%20in%20Applied%20Science%2C%20which%20was%20tailor-made%20to%20help%20students%20%26quot%3Bstay%20abreast%20of%20industry%20trends%2C%20technology%20changes%2C%20and%20job%20forecasts.%26quot%3B%20In%20the%202021-2022%20academic%20year%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Texas%20at%20Austin%20handed%20out%20114%20bachelor's%20degrees%20in%20individualized%20studies%2C%20an%20increase%20of%2041%25%20from%20the%20previous%20year%3B%20and%20at%20institutions%20that%20don't%20traditionally%20offer%20individualized-study%20programs%2C%20such%20as%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%2C%20students%20are%20going%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.teenvogue.com%2Fstory%2Fcreate-own-major-college%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreate%20their%20own%20majors%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdopting%20a%20rather%20divergent%20approach%20to%20the%20same%20goal%2C%20New%20York%20University's%20Gallatin%20School%20of%20Individualized%20Studies%20frames%20its%20approach%20as%20honing%20the%20%26quot%3Bmanagement%20of%20knowledge.%26quot%3B%20It%20differs%20from%20RIT%20by%20offering%20interdisciplinary%20seminars%20rather%20than%20skill-based%20courses%2C%20including%20classes%20like%20Baseball%20as%20a%20Road%20to%20God%2C%20Ethics%20for%20Dissenters%2C%20and%20Life%20Among%20Machines.%20Peter%20Rajsingh%2C%20a%20former%20Gallatin%20adjunct%20professor%2C%20firmly%20believes%20that%20by%20teaching%20students%20to%20draw%20on%20useful%20ideas%20from%20different%20areas%20of%20study%2C%20Gallatin%20helps%20students%20navigate%20unfamiliar%20situations%20and%20become%20more%20open-minded%2C%20making%20them%20more%20agile%20in%20the%20workforce.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKahrej%20Ahluwalia%2C%20who%20recently%20graduated%20from%20Gallatin%20with%20a%20concentration%20in%20Human-Computer%20Interaction%2C%20applied%20because%20of%20his%20appetite%20for%20flexible%20learning%20and%20a%20%26quot%3Bdirectional%20sense%20of%20interest%20in%20a%20blend%20of%20digital%20technology%2C%20philosophy%2C%20and%20psychology.%26quot%3B%20His%20time%20at%20Gallatin%20helped%20him%20land%20on%20a%20more%20focused%20discipline%20while%20allowing%20him%20flexibility%2C%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20international%20growth%20associate%20for%20an%20e-commerce%20startup%2C%20Ahluwalia%20said%20that%20his%20day-to-day%20involves%20responding%20to%20different%20market%20indicators%20to%20identify%20big-picture%20trends.%20At%20Gallatin%2C%20he%20said%20he%20learned%20to%20%26quot%3Bnavigate%20through%20ambiguity%2C%20be%20adaptable%20to%20change%2C%20and%20ultimately%20create%20structure%20where%20it%20doesn't%20exist%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20skills%20particularly%20relevant%20to%20his%20job.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20%E2%80%A6%20does%20it%20work%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIndividualized-study%20programs%20are%20designed%20to%20help%20students%20who%20are%20open%20to%20and%20actively%20seek%20help.%20In%20other%20words%3A%20You%20reap%20what%20you%20sow.%20For%20all%20the%20interdisciplinary%20courses%20and%20leadership%20and%20collaboration%20seminars%20offered%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bsuccess%26quot%3B%20of%20an%20individualized%20education%20boils%20down%20to%20what%20each%20student's%20goals%20are%20and%20whether%20faculty%20truly%20operate%20in%20a%20student's%20best%20interest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20describing%20the%20merits%20of%20these%20programs%2C%20faculty%20were%20also%20quick%20to%20point%20out%20their%20limitations.%20The%20focus%20on%20flexibility%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20traditional%20major%20track%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20leaves%20students%20more%20reliant%20on%20their%20relationship%20with%20professors%20and%20other%20school%20staff.%20Rajsingh%20said%20that%20very%20little%20guidance%20was%20given%20to%20faculty%20when%20crafting%20courses%20at%20Gallatin.%20Flexibility%20can%20empower%20educators%20to%20be%20creative%20with%20their%20approach%2C%20but%20Rajsingh%20said%20it%20also%20leaves%20ample%20room%20for%20bias.%20Rather%20than%20crafting%20courses%20that%20truly%20explore%20diverse%20ideas%20that%20challenge%20students%2C%20he%20said%20faculty%20members%20often%20end%20up%20serving%20only%20the%20%26quot%3Boptics%20of%20diversity%26quot%3B%20while%20furthering%20their%20own%20intellectual%20agenda.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20graduates%20are%20finding%20the%20approach%20successful.%20Either%20they%20land%20a%20unique%20job%20based%20on%20their%20customized%20degree%20or%20they%20maintain%20the%20flexibility%20to%20explore%20diverse%20career%20paths.%20At%20Gallatin%2C%2051%25%20of%20graduates%20go%20on%20to%20seek%20advanced%20degrees%20and%2080%25%20said%20their%20Gallatin%20concentration%20is%20connected%20to%20their%20current%20or%20past%20work.%20At%20RIT%2C%2085%25%20of%20graduates%20immediately%20enter%20the%20workforce%2C%20mostly%20in%20fields%20related%20to%20tech%20and%20design.%20Students%20at%20RIT%20are%20also%20turning%20their%20degrees%20into%20unique%20opportunities%2C%20such%20as%20building%20their%20own%20businesses%20in%20fields%20like%20textile-making%20or%20sustainable%20chocolate%20production.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuilding%20your%20own%20major%20is%20not%20for%20everyone%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20sign%20that%20precarity%20is%20the%20new%20norm.%20Students%20who%20graduate%20with%20unique%20degrees%20that%20they%20designed%20themselves%20gain%20the%20ability%20to%20pivot.%20And%20in%20today's%20environment%20of%20rapid%20change%20and%20AI-induced%20job%20insecurity%2C%20resilience%20in%20the%20form%20of%20flexibility%20is%20key.%20Schools%20like%20RIT%20and%20NYU%20are%20working%20to%20prepare%20students%20for%20uncertainty.%20Students%2C%20then%2C%20decide%20whether%20to%20sink%20or%20swim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Ftiffany-ng%5C%22%3ETiffany%20Ng%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20freelance%20tech%20and%20culture%20writer%20based%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-build-your-own-college-degrees-customized-major-jobs-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696500121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651db62c2ce014759e750035%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-build-your-own-college-degrees-customized-major-jobs-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gen%20Z%20students%20are%20turning%20to%20customized%20majors%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20changing%20economy%20and%20stay%20competitive%20in%20a%20chaotic%20job%20market.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Tiffany%20Ng)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A28%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-build-your-own-college-degrees-customized-major-jobs-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Founder%20Of%20China's%20BYD%20Drank%20Battery%20Fluid%20To%20Impress%20Warren%20Buffet%20Aide%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWang%20Chuanfu%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Chinese%20automaker%20BYD%2C%20has%20become%20a%20big%20name%20in%20the%20automobile%20industry.%20BYD%20is%20quickly%20gaining%20on%20Elon%20Musk's%20Tesla%20in%20the%20electric%20vehicle%20(EV)%20space%20to%20be%20the%20number%201.%20But%20now%2C%20a%20report%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20(WSJ)%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20said%20that%20Mr%20Wang%20drank%20a%20glass%20full%20of%20battery%20fluid%20to%20impress%20a%20member%20of%20investor%20Warren%20Buffet's%20team%2C%20who%20had%20reached%20Shenzhen%20to%20check%20if%20the%20company%20is%20worth%20investing%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBYD%20-%20short%20for%20'Build%20Your%20Dreams'%20-%20first%20launched%20as%20a%20battery%20maker%20in%20the%201995%20but%20in%202003%2C%20pivoted%20from%20being%20the%20world's%20largest%20manufacturer%20of%20rechargeable%20mobile%20phone%20batteries%20to%20the%20automotive%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20now%20on%20track%20to%20beat%20Tesla%20in%20terms%20of%20vehicle%20sales%2C%20as%20per%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%20(FT)%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20July%2C%20%3Cem%3EForbes%3C%2Fem%3E%20even%20reported%20that%20BYD's%20stock%20jumped%2090%20per%20cent%20despite%20the%20ongoing%20Covid-19%20cases%20in%20the%20country%20as%20he%20raked%20in%20US%20%247%20billion.%20His%20personal%20wealth%20is%20valued%20at%20over%20US%20%2425%20billion%2C%20which%20makes%20him%20currently%20the%2022nd%20richest%20person%20in%20China%2C%20per%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20automobile%20business%2C%20he%20replicated%20the%20way%20he%20made%20batteries%20to%20keep%20costs%20down.%20Mr%20Wang's%20business%20model%20attracted%20the%20attention%20of%20Mr%20Buffet%20and%20in%202008%2C%20he%20sent%20one%20of%20his%20aides%20David%20Sokol%20to%20Shenzhen%20to%20check%20out%20BYD.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Wang%20saw%20an%20opportunity%20to%20expand%20to%20other%20markets%2C%20like%20the%20US%2C%20and%20took%20the%20visitor%20through%20his%20factories.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20point%20during%20the%20tour%2C%20while%20trying%20to%20impress%20Mr%20Sokol%20about%20how%20BYD's%20batteries%20were%20safe%20for%20environment%2C%20poured%20himself%20a%20glass%20of%20battery%20fluid%20and%20took%20a%20sip%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fautos%2Fhow-chinas-byd-became-teslas-biggest-threat-5edfd080%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWSJ%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%20in%20its%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20mixture%20did%20not%20taste%20good%20and%20the%20US%20businessman%20declined%20the%20offer%20to%20try%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20September%20that%20year%2C%20Mr%20Buffet-owned%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%20bought%20a%2010%20per%20cent%20stake%20in%20BYD%20for%20%24232%20million%20via%20its%20energy%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMr%20Wang%2C%20born%20in%201966%20in%20Anhui%20province%2C%20was%20raised%20by%20older%20siblings%20after%20both%20his%20parents%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696500120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2F5mf37p6o_china-byd-reuters_625x300_05_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffounder-of-chinas-tesla-rival-byd-once-drank-battery-fluid-to-impress-warren-buffet-aide-report-4452439%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22BYD%20is%20now%20on%20track%20to%20beat%20Tesla%20in%20terms%20of%20vehicle%20sales%2C%20as%20per%20Financial%20Times%20(FT).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffounder-of-chinas-tesla-rival-byd-once-drank-battery-fluid-to-impress-warren-buffet-aide-report-4452439%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffounder-of-chinas-tesla-rival-byd-once-drank-battery-fluid-to-impress-warren-buffet-aide-report-4452439%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffounder-of-chinas-tesla-rival-byd-once-drank-battery-fluid-to-impress-warren-buffet-aide-report-4452439%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bail%20an%20Exception%2C%20Not%20a%20Rule%20in%20NDPS%2C%20UAPA%20Cases%3A%20Tripura%20High%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F19195946%2FHC.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Tripura%20high%20court%20has%20said%20the%20general%20rule%20of%20%E2%80%98bail%20not%20jail%E2%80%99%20is%20not%20applicable%20to%20those%20accused%20in%20cases%20registered%20under%20the%20Narcotic%20Drugs%20and%20Psychotropic%20Substances%20Act%20(NDPS%20Act)%20and%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20NDPS%20Act%20cases%2C%20Justice%20Arindham%20Lodh%20observed%20that%20stringent%20provisions%20of%20the%20law%20make%20bail%20an%20exception%20rather%20than%20a%20rule%2C%20%3Cem%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Ftripura-high-court-uapa-ndps-bail-exception-notrule%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20on%20a%20number%20of%20occasions%2C%20has%20highlighted%20that%20bail%20should%20be%20the%20rule%20and%20jail%20an%20exception%20to%20prevent%20%E2%80%9Cunnecessary%20arrests%E2%80%9D.%20The%20principle%20was%20first%20laid%20down%20by%20the%20apex%20court%20during%20the%20landmark%20judgment%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F8258%2F%5C%22%3EState%20of%20Rajasthan%20V.%20Balchand%20alias%20Baliay%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecase%20in%201978.%20Former%20judge%20V.R.%20Krishna%20Iyer%20had%20held%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20basic%20rule%20may%20perhaps%20be%20tersely%20put%20as%20bail%2C%20not%20jail.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Justice%20Lodh%20held%20that%20jail%20is%20the%20rule%20in%20the%20case%20of%20NDPS%20and%20UAPA%20cases.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6courts%20should%20not%20forget%20the%20rigours%20of%20NDPS%20and%20UAPA%20Act%20where%20it%20is%2C%20by%20now%20well%20settled%20that%20bail%20is%20not%20a%20rule%2C%20but%2C%20an%20exception%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Lodh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20took%20exception%20to%20lower%20courts%20dealing%20with%20NDPS%20cases%20%E2%80%9Cirresponsibly%20and%20rampantly%E2%80%9D%20granting%20bail%20to%20accused%20persons%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20procedural%20violations.%20He%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20procedural%20violations%20or%20irregularities%20should%20not%20be%20considered%20when%20deciding%20on%20bail%20pleas%20of%20those%20accused%20in%20NDPS%20and%20UAPA%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EJustice%20Lodh%20said%20granting%20bail%20in%20NDPS%20cases%20citing%20procedural%20issues%20amounts%20to%20a%20violation%20of%20Section%2037%20of%20the%20NDPS%20Act.%20The%20particular%20Section%20of%20the%20Act%20lays%20down%20limitations%20with%20regard%20to%20granting%20bail.%20The%20judge%20said%20procedural%20violations%20should%20be%20considered%20only%20during%20the%20trial%20stage%2C%20not%20at%20the%20bail%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%E2%80%99s%20observations%20were%20made%20during%20a%20hearing%20on%20the%20Tripura%20government%E2%80%99s%20plea%2C%20which%20sought%20cancellation%20of%20bail%20granted%20to%20three%20accused%20persons%20in%20an%20NDPS%20case.%20The%20government%20held%20that%20bail%20granted%20to%20the%20accused%20was%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20NDPS%20Act%2C%20while%20alleging%20that%20the%20accused%20were%20habitual%20offenders%20in%20the%20trade%20of%20illicit%20substances.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLearned%20Special%20Judge%20did%20not%20consider%20at%20all%20the%20twin%20conditions%20as%20embodied%20in%20Section%2037%20of%20the%20NDPS%20Act%20and%20released%20the%20accused-respondents%20on%20bail%20on%20the%20erroneous%20conception%20that%20since%20there%20were%20procedural%20violations%2Firregularities%2C%20the%20accused%E2%80%93respondents%C2%A0were%20entitled%20to%20get%20the%20benefit%20of%20bail%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAllowing%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20appeal%2C%20the%20high%20court%20noted%20that%20the%20trial%20court%20had%20%E2%80%9Ctotally%20misdirected%20and%20misread%20the%20provisions%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Act%20in%20releasing%20the%20accused%20on%20bail.%20%C2%A0The%20court%20ordered%20two%20of%20the%20accused%2C%20out%20on%20bail%2C%20to%20surrender%20while%20the%20third%20accused%20is%20still%20in%20jail%20in%20relation%20to%20another%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696500037000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F19195946%2FHC.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbail-an-exception-not-a-rule-in-ndps-uapa-cases-says-tripura-high-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'...courts%20should%20not%20forget%20the%20rigours%20of%20NDPS%20and%20UAPA%20Act%20where%20it%20is%2C%20by%20now%20well%20settled%20that%20bail%20is%20not%20a%20rule%2C%20but%2C%20an%20exception%2C'%20said%20Justice%20Arind