s%20Arrested%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F09132731%2Fnewsclick.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Delhi%20Police%20on%20Thursday%20(October%205)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fbarandbench%2Fstatus%2F1709810786544054758%5C%22%3Eopposed%20%3Cem%3ENewsclick%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Efounder%20and%20editor%20Prabir%20Purkayastha%E2%80%99s%20plea%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20provided%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20FIR%20under%20which%20he%20has%20been%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Farticle%2F1057116%2Fwhy-is-newsclick-being-denied-fir-copy-even-as-it-is-leaked-to-the-media%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EScroll%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Special%20Public%20Prosecutor%20Atul%20Shrivastava%20called%20the%20application%20%E2%80%9Cpremature%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20said%20that%20the%20accused%20must%20approach%20the%20police%20commissioner%20rather%20than%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPurkayastha%20and%20the%20head%20of%20the%20portal%E2%80%99s%20HR%20department%2C%20Amit%20Chakraborty%2C%20were%20arrested%20under%20the%20draconian%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20late%20on%20Tuesday%20after%20the%20Delhi%20Police%E2%80%99s%20Special%20Cell%20conducted%20raids%20at%20the%20residences%20of%20around%2046%20journalists%20and%20others%2C%20and%20confiscated%20all%20their%20devices.%20Some%20of%20the%20journalists%20were%20also%20questioned%20for%20several%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAction%20against%20the%20portal%20continued%20on%20Thursday%2C%20when%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20went%20to%20the%20home%20of%20a%20contractor%20who%20had%20worked%20on%20the%20publication%E2%80%99s%20office%20space%20and%20took%20him%20to%20the%20police%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20large-scale%20action%20and%20arrests%2C%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20refused%20to%20give%20%3Cem%3ENewsclick%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20lawyers%