ths%20of%20the%20warmest%20calendar%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%202016%2C%20by%200.05%C2%A0C.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20mean%20temperature%20so%20far%20this%20year%20is%201.40%20C%C2%A0higher%20than%20the%20preindustrial%20average%20between%201850%20and%201900.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20sense%20of%20urgency%20for%20ambitious%20climate%20action%20has%20never%20been%20more%20critical%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Samantha%20Burgess%2C%20deputy%20director%20of%20C3S%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20the%20report%E2%80%99s%20release%20comes%20just%20two%20months%20ahead%20of%20UN%20climate%20talks%20in%20Dubai.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EScientists%20say%20climate%20change%20caused%20by%20the%20burning%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20is%20making%20extreme%20weather%20such%20as%20heat%20waves%20and%20storms%20more%20intense%20and%20frequent.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20does%20the%20report%20say%20about%20September%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%C2%A0the%20report%2C%20September%202023%20was%20the%20warmest%20September%20on%20record.%20Average%20surface%20air%20temperature%20reached%2016.38%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20which%20is%200.93%20C%C2%A0above%20the%20monthly%20average%20during%201991-2020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%200.5%20C%C2%A0warmer%20than%20the%20previous%20warmest%20September%20to%20date%2C%20in%202020.%20That%20month%20was%20roughly%201.75%20C%C2%A0warmer%20than%20the%20September%20average%20of%20the%20preindustrial%20reference%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20unprecedented%20temperatures%20for%20the%20time%20of%20year%20observed%20in%20September%20%E2%80%93%20following%20a%20record%20summer%20%E2%80%93%20have%20broken%20records%20by%20an%20extraordinary%20amount%2C%E2%80%9D%20Burgess%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20described%20the%20month%20as%20%E2%80%9Cextreme%E2%80%9D%2C%20crediting%20it%20for%20pushing%202023%20%E2%80%9Cinto%20the%20dubious%20honour%20of%20first%20place%20%E2%80%93%20on%20track%20to%20be%20the%20warmest%20year%20and%20around%201.4%20C%20above%20preindustrial%20average%20temperatures.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Wetter-than-average%E2%80%99%20September%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Europe%2C%20the%20month%20was%20not%20only%20the%20hottest%20on%20record%20but%20also%20one%20with%20%E2%80%9Cwetter-than-average%E2%80%9D%20conditions%20along%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20continent%E2%80%99s%20western%20seaboard%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fclimate-change-fueled-flooding-in-libya-greece-bulgaria-study%2Fa-66862911%5C%22%3Ecited%20the%20extreme%20rainfall%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20Greece%2C%20associated%20with%20Storm%20Daniel.%20The%20storm%20also%20caused%20devastating%20flooding%20in%20Libya%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Flibya-thousands-feared-dead-after-storm-daniel%2Fa-66783443%5C%22%3Ekilling%20thousands%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20largely%20destroying%20its%20eastern%20city%20of%20Derna.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOther%20areas%20affected%20by%20rain%20in%20Europe%20include%C2%A0the%20western%20Iberian%20Peninsula%2C%20Ireland%2C%20northern%20Britain%2C%20and%20Scandinavia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBeyond%20Europe%2C%20the%20Latin%20American%20countries%20of%20Brazil%20and%20Chile%20also%20experienced%20what%20the%20report%20said%20were%20%E2%80%9Cextreme%20precipitation%20events%E2%80%9D%2C%20in%20the%20countries%E2%80%99%20southern%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20C3S%20is%20implemented%20by%20the%20European%20Center%20for%20Medium-Range%20Weather%20Forecasts%20on%20Behalf%20of%20the%20European%20Commission.%20It%20is%20funded%20by%20the%20EU.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20service%20said%20the%20findings%20are%20all%20based%20on%20computer-generated%20analyses%2C%20using%20measurements%20from%20satellites%2C%20ships%2C%20aircraft%20and%20weather%20stations%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fe